; DOMAIN: domain-theory/fixed-point [CLOSED, derived 2026-07-24 from G624 Domain-Theory-via-NAL] ; Claim: every Scott-continuous map on a pointed dcpo has a least fixed point. ; Structure: (dcpo D bottom) (scott-continuous f) ; Result: lfp(f) = sup{ f^n(bottom) | n in Nat } (Kleene ascending chain). ; Minimal: least-fixed-point = supremum of the bottom-iteration chain. ; Bridge: denotational value of a recursive program term = lfp of its Scott-continuous functional. (= (lfp $f) (sup (iterate $f bottom)))